                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <p><br>
                    <strong>Acceptable numeracy/ language qualifications for 
                      HLTA status</strong></p>
                    <p>What are acceptable  qualifications?</p>
                    <p>Acceptable level 2 qualifications to meet  standard 2.6 are:</p>
                    <table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Qualification type</p></td>
                        <td width="232" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Literacy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p></td>
                        <td width="255" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Numeracy</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>GCSE</p></td>
                        <td width="232" class="bodytext"><p>English A*- C<br>
                        English literature A*- C</p></td>
                        <td width="255" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Mathematics A*- C</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" class="bodytext"><p>Basic skills</p></td>
                        <td width="232" class="bodytext"><p>Certificate in adult literacy level 2</p></td>
                        <td width="255" class="bodytext"><p>Certificate in adult numeracy level 2</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" class="bodytext"><p>Key skills</p></td>
                        <td width="232" class="bodytext"><p>Communication level 2</p></td>
                        <td width="255" class="bodytext"><p>Application of number level 2</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" class="bodytext"><p>ESOL</p></td>
                        <td width="232" class="bodytext"><p>Skills for life qualifications level 2</p></td>
                        <td width="255" class="bodytext"><p>&nbsp;</p></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>
                    <p>Evidence of attainment of some level 3  qualifications may also meet standard 2.6. Acceptable level 3 qualifications  are:</p>
                    <table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Qualification type</p></td>
                        <td width="216" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Literacy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p></td>
                        <td width="240" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Numeracy</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>GCE A-level</p></td>
                        <td width="216" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>English language<br>
                          English literature<br>
                        English language and literature</p></td>
                        <td width="240" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Use of mathematics<br>
                          Mathematics<br>
                          Further mathematics<br>
                        Statistics</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>GCE AS-level</p></td>
                        <td width="216" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>English language<br>
                          English literature<br>
                        English language and literature</p></td>
                        <td width="240" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Mathematics<br>
                          Use of mathematics<br>
                          Further mathematics<br>
                          Pure mathematics<br>
                          Statistics<br>
                          Mechanics<br>
                          Applied mathematics<br>
                        Discrete mathematics</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td width="127" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Key skills</p></td>
                        <td width="216" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Communication level 3</p></td>
                        <td width="240" valign="top" class="bodytext"><p>Application of number level 3</p></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>
                    <p>What do I do if I  don&rsquo;t have any of the above qualifications?</p>
                    <p>Adult  Numeracy and Literacy level 2 tests are widely available and held at regular  intervals. For further information, please visit <a href="http://www.dfes.gov.uk/readwriteplus/learning">www.dfes.gov.uk/readwriteplus/learning</a> or <a href="http://www.learndirect.co.uk/">Learn Direct</a>.</p>
                    <p><br>
                    </p>
